race.comment: Tough. HIT (10) pushed forward and was improved first-up beaten a nose over 1000m at Sunshine Coast. Draws wider today but keeps the 2kg claim and has been kept on the fresh side. Has his first go on a poly track and rates an each-way proposition. SIGLO DE ORO (3) recorded a strong Maiden win here scoring by a whopping 7L. Relished his first run on the poly and will ride the speed again. Will get every chance to take the next step. CAT CALL (9) resumes and is right up to this if presented forward. Has won here over the trip and has the blinkers on for the first time signalling intent. Positions forward and will get every chance. SHIPPING LANE (5) did a good job winning his Maiden at the track. Will hit this at peak fitness and has claims as well.
